jobs_results.title: IOS Developer
jobs_results.description:
We're revolutionising traditional banking with our innovative products and exceptional customer service.
About Our Mobile Engineering Practice

Our team of mobile engineers is comprised of individuals from diverse backgrounds.

We work in project-based sprints, collaborating in small, interdisciplinary teams to drive progress.

We're seeking skilled iOS engineers with a passion for UI/UX to join our team. As an iOS engineer at Monzo, you'll contribute to a small, autonomous product squad alongside other talented professionals.

Your primary objective will be aligned with the company's overall goals, allowing you to have a significant impact on both the features we build and how we develop them.

You'll have the opportunity to work with industry-standard tools and technologies, helping us establish new standards for iOS engineering.

Our architecture is built upon Alamofire, utilising a generic interface to efficiently de-serialise objects of specific types.

We employ a micro-service architecture in our backend, mirroring this by creating individual services to house our API logic.

Our testing framework consists of unit tests for business logic, stubbed API tests for pseudo-integration tests, snapshot tests for UI, and XCUITest for user input and sequencing.
• You are passionate about programming in Swift.
• You've successfully shipped and iterated on at least one app in the App Store.
• You possess a product mindset, prioritising customer outcomes and making informed decisions based on data.
• You have a solid understanding of computer science principles.
What We Offer

We provide flexible working hours, trusting you to work enough hours to excel in your role, while also respecting your personal schedule.

We offer a £1,000 annual learning budget for books, training courses, and conferences.

If you prefer part-time work, we'll accommodate your needs whenever possible – whether to support other commitments or achieve a better work-life balance.

We can assist with relocation to the UK and sponsor visas, although remote work outside of the UK is currently not supported.
Equal Opportunities for Everyone

Diversity and inclusion are essential aspects of our company culture. We foster an inclusive environment where all individuals can grow and thrive with us. All applicants will be considered for employment without bias towards age, ethnicity, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, family or parental status, national origin, veteran status, neurodiversity, or disability status.

jobs_results.title: Mac OSX / iOS Developer / 3D Programmer
jobs_results.description:
This position would suit a talented Mac programmer with the ability to develop and implement UI using objective C, contribute throughout the development life cycle and is looking to work in a stimulating environment with like minded people. Joining a creative and inspiring team, you will be responsible for programming using Objective C and some C++ in the Cocoa environment as well as driving to develop apps on the IOS platform. There will also be room for growth within the company... As we grow, you'll grow!

Your duties will include:
Developing applications, interface, design and implementation, source control, formulating new concepts, debugging and product maintenance. You will also be expected to communicate your findings to others as well as provide technical expertise on concepts.

To be considered for this position, you must have:
Macintosh programming experience in the Cocoa environment, fluency in objective C, experience of the full Mac product life cycle and some iOS experience. You must be familiar with handling source on various projects and experience with SVN version control or similar. You must have good communication skills both verbal and written.

Considered a positive if you:
Have an aptitude for mathematics, in particular 3D co-ordinate geometry, trigonometry and transform matrices. An interest in working with 2D and 3D consumer based graphical applications, IOS development skills. Have experience with the Adobe products or simiar vector design programs and knowledge of web technologies such as HTML, CSS, Java, JQuery, MySQL and PHP.

jobs_results.title: iOS Researcher (Remote)
jobs_results.description:
This a Full Remote job, the offer is available from: United Kingdom

Description

Company Overview:

Cellebrite’s (Nasdaq: CLBT) mission is to enable its customers to protect and save lives, accelerate justice, and preserve privacy in communities around the world. Cellebrite is a global leader in Digital Intelligence solutions for the public and private sectors, empowering organizations to master the complexities of legally sanctioned digital investigations by streamlining intelligence processes. Trusted by thousands of leading agencies and companies globally, Cellebrite’s Digital Intelligence platform and solutions transform how customers collect, review, analyze, and manage investigative digital data in legally sanctioned investigations.

﻿

Position Overview:

Cellebrite is looking for talented researchers to join the industry’s leading digital intelligence Security Research Labs group. As a security researcher in our team, you will be taking part in leading new projects.

Key responsibilities:
• Research on territories with little-explored vulnerability
• Work on the production of world-unique capabilities to extract evidence from phones and other embedded devices.
• iPhones and other iOS devices present tough challenges from a forensics perspective and involve hardware-backed encryption (SiDP), secure crypto coprocessor (SEP), and secured boot chain (SecureROM).
• New iPhones present state-of-the-art exploit mitigations such as PAC, KTRR, and PPL.
• Become a member of Labs Group, focusing on Security Research for mobile devices.
• Execute your shell code on top-notch technology mobile platforms hardened with challenging mitigations
• Collaborate with a team of passionate researchers dedicated to solving modern digital intelligence challenges, years ahead of others in the industry.
• Take part in world-class research results, assisting law enforcement by enabling lawful evidence extraction, and putting criminals behind bars every day.

Qualifications:
• Proven vulnerability research experience (preferably in iOS) - Must
• Experience with advanced exploitation techniques
• ARM reverse engineering - Must
• Cryptographic primitives and weaknesses
• Hardware research/board design - Advantage
• You are a security researcher who cares about the ethical values of your work
• You love the art of engineering and crafting a platform-wide native payload, in a fragmented ecosystem of gaping variance
• You are passionate about technology and keen to use your skills to make the world a safer place

This offer from "Cellebrite" has been enriched by Jobgether.com and got a 81% flex score.

jobs_results.title: IOS Developer
jobs_results.description:
About Us

TrustFlight is an innovative aviation software company that specialises in developing cutting-edge digital workflow and analytics applications for the aviation industry. Our software empowers airlines, airports, and aviation service providers to optimise their operations, enhance safety, and improve overall efficiency.

We are looking for an up-and-coming Junior iOS Developer to join our dynamic team and contribute to our growing suite of mobile apps within the organisation.
Job Description

As a Junior iOS Developer you will support our SaaS products focused on digital workflows and document management. Whilst iOS (Swift) development will be your primary focus, there will likely be some exposure to Android as well. You will closely follow the rapid advances in AI capabilities and be keen to use your firm grasp of AI tooling to accelerate your personal growth.

You will work alongside software engineers, data engineers and AI engineers to ensure that our digital workflows become more innovative and highly automated with augmented decision support for our customers.

We value each member's input and believe in harnessing the power of collective intelligence, with each team member's contribution playing a crucial role in our success.
The Role
• Develop iOS (Swift) applications for our SaaS products, with the potential for occasional Android work.
• Maintain CI/CD pipelines to ensure swift delivery of reliable builds.
• Use test automation, TestFlight and collaborate with QA Engineers to ensure all deliverables are robustly tested prior to release to meet quality KPIs.
• Work closely across Software Development teams to facilitate integration of our iOS applications, maximise the use of AI, shape best practice and ensure alignment with overall mobile strategy.
• Support Technical Leads and Product Managers to assess requirements and identify appropriate solutions.
• Collaborate with Product Designers to ensure our design system is accurately applied.

Job Type: Full-time

Salary: £55,000 - £65,000 per annum

Location: Leamington Spa, UK
Requirements
• Hands-on experience of iOS (Swift) development and/or demonstrable evidence of leveraging AI tooling to rapidly craft mobile or web applications.
• Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field.
• Experience of Android (Kotlin) development, or the ability to pick it up quickly as required.
• Strong understanding of the capabilities, scope, and limitations of the current state of AI, particularly in a mobile context.
• Experience in problem solving prompt engineering.
• A quality mindset, recognising that quality is everybody's responsibility, and driven by a desire to deliver the best possible experience to customers.
• Natural leadership skills, inspiring those you work with to collectively achieve outstanding results.
• Ability to communicate effectively with non-technical stakeholders.
